content.description:
There's an easier problem on the left side of the face that eviction notice is on.  Left of the A frame between the two boulders, in the little cave.   

  Don't know much more about it

The holds are all there, and the moves into the stand aren't all that hard by themselves.  but with how weird the dyno is, and how slippery the V shaped crimp is, the difficulty will come from being set up badly and more tired by the time you dyno. 

  Get after it!

On the right side of the overhanging face, right of the cave.  Start standing on a slopey, slippery V-shaped crimp edge, figure out your footwork and blast up to a sharp, flat jug above.  This dyno requires power as well as being a somewhat technical weird move.  You have to push with your feet just right, otherwise you will be evicted onto the pads.  

  Easier top moves are a bit more real than they look, I wouldn't advise falling off onto the boulder behind you.
content.location: Right side of the overhanging face, just right of the cave.

content.description: This is the overhanging face uphill from the obvious large dihedral boulder that has a bolt on it.  The problems are on the overhanging face that leans against the back of the dihedral boulder.
